preamble.title: solvernet/protocol
preamble.description: SolverNet DEX - Intent-Based Decentralized Exchange for Cardano

anyOf.title: Some
anyOf.description: An optional value.

anyOf.title: None
anyOf.description: Nothing.

cardano/address/Address.title: Address
cardano/address/Address.description:
A Cardano `Address` typically holding one or two credential references.

 Note that legacy bootstrap addresses (a.k.a. 'Byron addresses') are
 completely excluded from Plutus contexts. Thus, from an on-chain
 perspective only exists addresses of type 00, 01, ..., 07 as detailed
 in [CIP-0019 :: Shelley Addresses](https://github.com/cardano-foundation/CIPs/tree/master/CIP-0019/#shelley-addresses).

cardano/address/Credential.title: Credential
cardano/address/Credential.description:
A general structure for representing an on-chain `Credential`.

 Credentials are always one of two kinds: a direct public/private key
 pair, or a script (native or Plutus).

cardano/address/PaymentCredential.title: PaymentCredential
cardano/address/PaymentCredential.description:
A general structure for representing an on-chain `Credential`.

 Credentials are always one of two kinds: a direct public/private key
 pair, or a script (native or Plutus).

cardano/address/StakeCredential.title: StakeCredential
cardano/address/StakeCredential.description:
Represent a type of object that can be represented either inline (by hash)
 or via a reference (i.e. a pointer to an on-chain location).

 This is mainly use for capturing pointers to a stake credential
 registration certificate in the case of so-called pointer addresses.

cardano/transaction/OutputReference.title: OutputReference
cardano/transaction/OutputReference.description:
An `OutputReference` is a unique reference to an output on-chain. The `output_index`
 corresponds to the position in the output list of the transaction (identified by its id)
 that produced that output

solvernet/types/AssetClass.title: AssetClass
solvernet/types/AssetClass.description:
Represents a native token identifier (policy ID + asset name).
 For ADA: use `ada_asset_class()`.

solvernet/types/EscrowDatum.title: EscrowDatum
solvernet/types/EscrowDatum.description:
Escrow datum  locks user funds with swap intent parameters.
 Each intent is a separate UTxO, eliminating eUTXO concurrency issues.

fields.title: escrow_token
fields.description: Auth token proving this is a legitimate escrow UTxO

fields.title: owner
fields.description: Owner of the intent (can cancel)

fields.title: input_asset
fields.description: Asset being offered (locked in this UTxO)

fields.title: input_amount
fields.description: Total amount originally offered

fields.title: output_asset
fields.description: Asset desired in return

fields.title: min_output
fields.description: Minimum acceptable output amount (slippage protection)

fields.title: deadline
fields.description: Deadline (POSIX time ms). After this, anyone can reclaim to owner.

fields.title: max_partial_fills
fields.description: Maximum number of partial fills allowed (prevents griefing)

fields.title: fill_count
fields.description: Number of fills already executed

fields.title: remaining_input
fields.description: Remaining input amount (decreases with partial fills)

solvernet/types/EscrowRedeemer.title: EscrowRedeemer
solvernet/types/EscrowRedeemer.description: Actions that can be performed on an escrow UTxO.

anyOf.title: Cancel
anyOf.description: Owner cancels the intent and reclaims funds

anyOf.title: Fill
anyOf.description: Solver fills the intent (partially or fully)

fields.title: input_consumed
fields.description: Amount of input asset consumed in this fill

fields.title: output_delivered
fields.description: Amount of output asset delivered to owner

anyOf.title: Reclaim
anyOf.description: Reclaim expired intent (anyone can trigger, funds go to owner)

solvernet/types/FactoryDatum.title: FactoryDatum
solvernet/types/FactoryDatum.description:
Factory global state  stored at the single factory UTxO.
 The factory tracks pool creation and ensures trading pair uniqueness.

fields.title: factory_nft
fields.description: NFT identifying this factory UTxO (thread token)

fields.title: pool_count
fields.description: Monotonically increasing pool counter

fields.title: admin
fields.description: Admin verification key hash (governs factory operations)

fields.title: settings_utxo
fields.description: Reference to the settings UTxO for protocol params

solvernet/types/FactoryRedeemer.title: FactoryRedeemer
solvernet/types/FactoryRedeemer.description: Actions that can be performed on the factory.

anyOf.title: CreatePool
anyOf.description: Create a new liquidity pool

fields.title: asset_a
fields.description: First asset of the trading pair

fields.title: asset_b
fields.description: Second asset of the trading pair

fields.title: initial_a
fields.description: Initial deposit of asset A

fields.title: initial_b
fields.description: Initial deposit of asset B

fields.title: fee_numerator
fields.description: Fee numerator (denominator = 10000)

anyOf.title: UpdateSettings
anyOf.description: Update factory settings (admin only)

solvernet/types/IntentTokenRedeemer.title: IntentTokenRedeemer
solvernet/types/IntentTokenRedeemer.description: Redeemer for the Intent Token minting policy.

anyOf.title: MintIntentToken
anyOf.description: Mint intent auth token (user creates intent)

fields.title: consumed_utxo
fields.description: TX output reference consumed to ensure uniqueness

anyOf.title: BurnIntentToken
anyOf.description: Burn intent auth token (fill or cancel)

solvernet/types/LPRedeemer.title: LPRedeemer
solvernet/types/LPRedeemer.description: Redeemer for the LP Token minting policy.

anyOf.title: MintOrBurnLP
anyOf.description: Mint or burn LP tokens (positive = mint, negative = burn)

fields.title: pool_nft
fields.description: Which pool this LP action belongs to

fields.title: amount
fields.description: Amount to mint (positive) or burn (negative)

solvernet/types/OrderDatum.title: OrderDatum
solvernet/types/OrderDatum.description:
Advanced order datum  supports limit orders, DCA, and stop-loss.
 These are long-lived UTxOs that can be partially filled over time.

fields.title: order_type
fields.description: Order type discriminator

fields.title: owner
fields.description: Owner address

fields.title: asset_in
fields.description: Input asset (being sold)

fields.title: asset_out
fields.description: Output asset (being bought)

fields.title: params
fields.description: Order-specific parameters

fields.title: order_token
fields.description: Auth token for this order

solvernet/types/OrderParams.title: OrderParams
solvernet/types/OrderParams.description: Parameters that govern order execution behavior.

fields.title: target_price_num
fields.description:
Target price as rational number (numerator, denominator)
 For LimitOrder: buy when price <= target (or sell when >=)

fields.title: amount_per_interval
fields.description: For DCA: amount per interval

fields.title: min_interval
fields.description: For DCA: minimum slot interval between fills

fields.title: last_fill_slot
fields.description: For DCA: slot of last fill execution

fields.title: remaining_budget
fields.description: Total remaining budget

fields.title: deadline
fields.description: Global deadline for the order

solvernet/types/OrderRedeemer.title: OrderRedeemer
solvernet/types/OrderRedeemer.description: Actions that can be performed on an order.

anyOf.title: CancelOrder
anyOf.description: Cancel the order (owner only)

anyOf.title: ExecuteOrder
anyOf.description: Execute/fill the order

fields.title: amount_consumed
fields.description: Amount consumed from budget

fields.title: output_delivered
fields.description: Amount of output asset delivered

anyOf.title: LimitOrder
anyOf.description: Execute when price reaches target

anyOf.title: DCA
anyOf.description: Dollar-cost averaging  periodic purchases

anyOf.title: StopLoss
anyOf.description: Execute when price drops below threshold

solvernet/types/PoolDatum.title: PoolDatum
solvernet/types/PoolDatum.description:
Pool state  each AMM pool has its own UTxO with this datum.
 Implements constant product (x*y=k) invariant.

fields.title: pool_nft
fields.description: Unique pool identifier (Pool NFT asset class)

fields.title: asset_a
fields.description: First asset in the trading pair (canonically ordered: A < B)

fields.title: asset_b
fields.description: Second asset in the trading pair

fields.title: total_lp_tokens
fields.description: Total LP tokens currently in circulation

fields.title: fee_numerator
fields.description:
Fee numerator (denominator is fixed at 10000)
 e.g., 30 = 0.3% fee per swap

fields.title: protocol_fees_a
fields.description: Accumulated protocol fees for asset A

fields.title: protocol_fees_b
fields.description: Accumulated protocol fees for asset B

fields.title: last_root_k
fields.description:
Root K = floor(sqrt(reserve_a * reserve_b)) at last state change.
 Used for manipulation resistance checks.

solvernet/types/PoolNFTRedeemer.title: PoolNFTRedeemer
solvernet/types/PoolNFTRedeemer.description: Redeemer for the Pool NFT minting policy.

anyOf.title: MintPoolNFT
anyOf.description: Mint a new pool NFT (during pool creation)

fields.title: consumed_utxo
fields.description: TX output reference consumed to ensure global uniqueness

anyOf.title: BurnPoolNFT
anyOf.description: Burn a pool NFT (pool closure  future feature)

solvernet/types/PoolRedeemer.title: PoolRedeemer
solvernet/types/PoolRedeemer.description: Actions that can be performed on a pool.

anyOf.title: Swap
anyOf.description: Execute a token swap against the pool

anyOf.title: Deposit
anyOf.description: Add liquidity to the pool (proportional deposit)

anyOf.title: Withdraw
anyOf.description: Remove liquidity from the pool (burn LP tokens)

anyOf.title: CollectFees
anyOf.description: Collect accumulated protocol fees (admin only)

anyOf.title: ClosePool
anyOf.description: Close the pool  admin burns the pool NFT and reclaims all reserves

solvernet/types/SettingsDatum.title: SettingsDatum
solvernet/types/SettingsDatum.description: Global protocol configuration  acts as read-only reference for other validators.

fields.title: admin
fields.description: Protocol admin (script hash for multi-sig)

fields.title: protocol_fee_bps
fields.description: Protocol fee in basis points (e.g., 5 = 0.05%)

fields.title: min_pool_liquidity
fields.description: Minimum initial pool liquidity in lovelace

fields.title: min_intent_size
fields.description: Minimum intent size in lovelace

fields.title: solver_bond
fields.description: Solver bond requirement in lovelace (future use)

fields.title: fee_collector
fields.description: Fee collector address

fields.title: version
fields.description: Protocol version (monotonically increasing)

anyOf.title: UpdateProtocolSettings
anyOf.description: Update protocol parameters (admin only)

anyOf.title: AToB
anyOf.description: Swap asset A for asset B

anyOf.title: BToA
anyOf.description: Swap asset B for asset A
